          <h2 style="font-size:24px;line-height:1.2;font-weight:500; margin-top:2px !important">Ukraine retreats from Kursk</h2>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-image border-radius="10px" padding="10px 12px" width="600px" src="https://www.geopoliticalsummary.com/email/images/sudzha-town-kursk-region-ukrainian-army-entry.png" alt="View of the town of Sudzha in Russia's Kursk region after the Ukrainian army entered the area" href="https://www.geopoliticalsummary.com" />
        <mj-text padding="0px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#A9A7AF">
          <p style="font-size: 12px; line-height: 1.2; color: #A9A7AF;"><i>View of the town of Sudzha in Russia's Kursk region after the Ukrainian army entered the area. Credits: Libkos/ Getty Images
          </i></p>
        </mj-text> 

        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
         
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">Ukraine has confirmed its <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-18-03-2025-h1-1-withdrawal-from-sudzha" target="_blank">withdrawal from Sudzha</a> in Russia's Kursk Oblast, days after Moscow claimed its capture. Kyiv had seized the town in August 2024, hoping to use it as leverage in negotiations, but mounting Russian pressure forced a retreat. Ukrainian forces face increasing challenges without this leverage. Russia is preparing an assault on Sumy, and Ukraine is struggling with manpower shortages.</p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">The General Staff of Ukraine posted the latest battlefield maps on social media, showing a complete retreat from Sudzha. Ukraine also brushed aside claims that President Trump urged Putin to spare allegedly surrounded Ukranian troops. The UK has proposed a 10,000-strong Western peacekeeping mission to secure Ukraine in a post-war scenario, though European allies remain divided on participation.  
       </p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">Meanwhile, President Trump is expected to speak with Russian President Vladimir Putin today. US envoy Steve Witkoff suggested a ceasefire could be reached within a week. However, Russia demands guarantees to limit Ukraine’s military actions, such as joining NATO. Ukraine appears keen only to make concessions if allowed to enter the NATO bloc. 

</p>
        </mj-text>
