        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="TNYAdobeCaslonPro, 'Times New Roman', serif;" color="#000000">
          <h2 style="font-size:24px;line-height:1.2;font-weight:500;">Ceasefire at risk</h2>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-image border-radius="10px" padding="10px 12px" width="600px" src="https://www.geopoliticalsummary.com/email/images/israel-airstrikes-gaza-strip-hamas-targets-69-deaths-ceasefire-broken.png" alt="Israel launched a wave of airstrikes across the Gaza Strip, striking dozens of Hamas targets in its heaviest assault in the territory since a ceasefire took effect. Palestinian officials reported at least 69 deaths" href="https://www.geopoliticalsummary.com" />
        <mj-text padding="0px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#A9A7AF">
          <p style="font-size: 12px; line-height: 1.2; color: #A9A7AF;"><i>Israel launched a wave of airstrikes across the Gaza Strip, striking dozens of Hamas targets in its heaviest assault in the territory since a ceasefire took effect. Palestinian officials reported at least 69 deaths. Credits: Wafaa Shurafaa</i></p>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000"> 
         
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">Overnight, Israel launched its largest <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.presidentialsummary.com/gs-18-03-2025-h2-2-wave-of-airstrikes-in-gaza" target="_blank">wave of airstrikes on Gaza</a>, nulling the ceasefire agreement. It targeted places that Israel referred to as Hamas "terror targets" in Gaza City, Rafah, and Khan Younis. At least 330 Palestinians have been killed, per the Gaza Health Ministry. Many of the casualties were women and children. 
</p>

          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">Civilians described scenes of devastation, bodies under rubble, and overwhelmed hospitals. One of the casualties was Mahmoud Abu Wafah, Gaza's Deputy Interior Minister and the highest-ranking Hamas security official. Additionally, the strikes hit as Palestinians were observing Ramadan, catching many civilians by surprise during their pre-dawn meals. The recent negotiations in Doha involving Egypt, Qatar, and the US collapsed after 72 hours.</p>

          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">Israel accused Hamas of refusing to release hostages and rejecting all diplomatic proposals. Israel’s leadership ordered the strikes, warning Hamas that "increasing military strength" would be used. Hamas condemned the move and has not officially declared a return to full-scale war but called on mediators and the UN to intervene. They have also called for a global boycott of Israel.</p>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-divider border-width="1px" border-style="solid" border-color="lightgrey" padding="0px 12px" />
