          <p style="font-size:18px;line-height:1.5;">
            <strong>🇷🇼 Rwanda severs ties with Belgium over row</strong>
          </p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">
          Rwanda has <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-18-03-2025-br1-4-severed-diplomatic-ties" target="_blank">severed diplomatic relations</a> with Belgium. Belgian diplomats are ordered to leave within 48 hours. This follows accusations that Belgium is undermining Rwanda over the M23 rebel offensive in eastern DR Congo. In response, Belgium declared Rwandan diplomats persona non grata. The dispute escalates as M23, allegedly backed by Rwanda, has seized key cities in eastern Congo since January.</p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">While Rwanda denies supporting the rebels, the UN estimates it has 4,000 troops in the region. Belgium has pushed the EU to suspend its 2024 raw materials deal with Rwanda. It is notable the former colonizer of both Rwanda and Congo. Peace talks between the Congolese government and M23 rebels are set to take place in Angola.</p>
        </mj-text>
