          <p style="font-size:18px;line-height:1.5;">
            <strong>🇪🇺 Rule of law in decline across the EU per report</strong>
          </p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">A recent report by the Civil Liberties Union for Europe shows a persistent decrease in the <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-18-03-2025-br2-5-rule-of-law" target="_blank">rule of law</a> across the EU. Some key issues include political manipulation of justice systems, weak anti-corruption efforts, shrinking media freedom, and threats to human rights. Countries like Hungary, Romania, and Italy face systemic rule of law erosion, while nations such as Estonia and the Czech Republic show signs of improvement.</p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">The report also warned that even model democracies like France and Germany face growing challenges, particularly concerning freedom of expression and political interference. The report calls for more decisive action by the European Commission while criticizing the EU’s weak enforcement mechanisms.</p>
        </mj-text>
